<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="375" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">
Northern and Central Europe, including Scandinavia, the Netherlands, Belgium, Germany, Switzerland, France as far south as Valensole and Avignon (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 55" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 55. Distribution map of Andrena gelriae (red dots), A. ovata (blue dots) and A. vocifera (green dots)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.91.82761.figure55" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/707514" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">55</figureCitation>
); southern Italy. The distribution in Central and Eastern Europe (e.g. Bulgaria, Romania, Austria, Poland), requires further examination due to confusion with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1973" class="Insecta" family="Fabaceae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena producta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="producta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Andrena producta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="gelriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion in 
<bibRefCitation author="Gusenleitner, F" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="211 - 276" refId="B12" refString="Gusenleitner, F, 1984. Faunistische und morphologische Angaben zu bemerkenswerten Andrena -Arten aus Österreich (Insecta: Apoidea: Andrenidae). Linzer biologische Beitraege 16: 211 - 276" title="Faunistische und morphologische Angaben zu bemerkenswerten Andrena - Arten aus O ̈ sterreich (Insecta: Apoidea: Andrenidae)." volume="16" year="1984">Gusenleitner 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="375" type="pollen preferences">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Pollen preferences.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">
Probably oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" refId="B78" refString="Westrich, P, 1989. Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs. Ulmer, Stuttgart" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
), although the difficulties in identifications prevent solid conclusions. In Switzerland the species was observed foraging on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Medicago" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Medicago" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Medicago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium pratense" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Trifolium pratense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DB and CJP, unpublished data).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="375" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">
Univoltine, in central Europe from early June until mid-July, slightly after 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. wilkella" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="wilkella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. wilkella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(although this species has a long flight period; see below) and 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in northern Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Niemelae, P" journalOrPublisher="Suomen hyoenteistieteellinen aikakauskirja = Annales entomologici Fennici" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="101 - 120" refId="B33" refString="Niemelae, P, 1949. Mitteilungen ueber die Apiden (Hym.) Finnlands. 3. Die Untergattung Taeniandrena Hedicke. Suomen hyoenteistieteellinen aikakauskirja = Annales entomologici Fennici 15: 101 - 120" title="Mitteilungen ueber die Apiden (Hym.) Finnlands. 3. Die Untergattung Taeniandrena Hedicke." volume="15" year="1949">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Niemelä">Niemelae</normalizedToken>
1949
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="375" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Eos" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="171 - 318" refId="B71" refString="Warncke, K, 1967. Beitrag zur Klärung paläarktischer Andrena -Arten (Hym. Apidae). Eos 43: 171 - 318" title="Beitrag zur Kla ̈ rung pala ̈ arktischer Andrena - Arten (Hym. Apidae)." volume="43" year="1967">Warncke (1967</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnz.4830490103" author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="13 - 36" refId="B73" refString="Warncke, K, 1973. Beitrag zur Bienenfauna Mazedoniens (Colletidae, Andrenidae und Melittidae / Apoidea). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 49: 13 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnz.4830490103" title="Beitrag zur Bienenfauna Mazedoniens (Colletidae, Andrenidae und Melittidae / Apoidea)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnz.4830490103" volume="49" year="1973">1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitschrift" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="133 - 136" refId="B74" refString="Warncke, K, 1975a. Ergänzungen zu den Verbreitungskarten der Bienengattung Andrena in Frankreich (Hymenoptea, Andrenidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift 85: 133 - 136" title="Erga ̈ nzungen zu den Verbreitungskarten der Bienengattung Andrena in Frankreich (Hymenoptea, Andrenidae)." volume="85" year="1975 a">1975a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Eos" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="293 - 314" refId="B75" refString="Warncke, K, 1975b. Die Bienengattung Andrena F., 1775, in Iberien (Hym. Apidae). Teil A. Eos 49: 293 - 314" title="Die Bienengattung Andrena F., 1775, in Iberien (Hym. Apidae). Teil A." volume="49" year="1975 b">1975b</bibRefCitation>
; see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Gusenleitner, F" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" refId="B13" refString="Gusenleitner, F, Schwarz, M, 2002. Weltweite Checkliste der Bienengattung Andrena mit Bemerkungen und Ergaenzungen zu Palaearktischen Arten. Entomofauna Suppl.12: 1-1280." title="Weltweite Checkliste der Bienengattung Andrena mit Bemerkungen und Ergaenzungen zu Palaearktischen Arten. Entomofauna Suppl. 12: 1 - 1280." year="2002">Gusenleitner and Schwarz 2002</bibRefCitation>
) considered 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="gelriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be composed of several subspecies distributed from Spain and Portugal (
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gredana" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="gredana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gredana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.758.1431" author="Wood, TJ" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="147 - 193" refId="B84" refString="Wood, TJ, Ghisbain, G, Michez, D, Praz, CJ, 2021. Revisions to the faunas of Andrena of the Iberian Peninsula and Morocco with the descriptions of four new species (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 758: 147 - 193, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.758.1431" title="Revisions to the faunas of Andrena of the Iberian Peninsula and Morocco with the descriptions of four new species (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.758.1431" volume="758" year="2021">Wood et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
), southern France (
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. vocifera" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="vocifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. vocifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Central and Northern Europe (
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="gelriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">sensu stricto</emphasis>
), Finland (
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae subsp. karelica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="subSpecies" species="gelriae" subSpecies="karelica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae karelica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Niemelä">Niemelae</normalizedToken>
, 1949) and Austria to south-eastern Europe and Turkey (
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. producta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="producta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. producta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Gusenleitner, F" journalOrPublisher="Linzer biologische Beitraege" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="211 - 276" refId="B12" refString="Gusenleitner, F, 1984. Faunistische und morphologische Angaben zu bemerkenswerten Andrena -Arten aus Österreich (Insecta: Apoidea: Andrenidae). Linzer biologische Beitraege 16: 211 - 276" title="Faunistische und morphologische Angaben zu bemerkenswerten Andrena - Arten aus O ̈ sterreich (Insecta: Apoidea: Andrenidae)." volume="16" year="1984">Gusenleitner (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Schwarz, M" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="301 - 372" refId="B58" refString="Schwarz, M, Gusenleitner, F, 1997. Neue und ausgewählte Bienenarten für Österreich. Vorstudie zu einer Gesamtbearbeitung der Bienen Österreichs (Hymenoptera, Apidae). Entomofauna 18: 301 - 372" title="Neue und ausgewa ̈ hlte Bienenarten fu ̈ r O ̈ sterreich. Vorstudie zu einer Gesamtbearbeitung der Bienen O ̈ sterreichs (Hymenoptera, Apidae)." volume="18" year="1997">Schwarz and Gusenleitner (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.758.1431" author="Wood, TJ" journalOrPublisher="European Journal of Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="147 - 193" refId="B84" refString="Wood, TJ, Ghisbain, G, Michez, D, Praz, CJ, 2021. Revisions to the faunas of Andrena of the Iberian Peninsula and Morocco with the descriptions of four new species (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae). European Journal of Taxonomy 758: 147 - 193, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.758.1431" title="Revisions to the faunas of Andrena of the Iberian Peninsula and Morocco with the descriptions of four new species (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5852/ejt.2021.758.1431" volume="758" year="2021">Wood et al (2021)</bibRefCitation>
have respectively demonstrated that 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. producta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="producta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. producta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gredana" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="gredana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gredana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent distinct species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Praz &amp; Genoud &amp; Vaucher &amp; Bénon &amp; Monks &amp; Wood" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Fabaceae" genus="Andrena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Andrena vocifera" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vocifera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">Andrena vocifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also raised here to a distinct species (see below). Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Niemelae, P" journalOrPublisher="Suomen hyoenteistieteellinen aikakauskirja = Annales entomologici Fennici" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" pagination="101 - 120" refId="B33" refString="Niemelae, P, 1949. Mitteilungen ueber die Apiden (Hym.) Finnlands. 3. Die Untergattung Taeniandrena Hedicke. Suomen hyoenteistieteellinen aikakauskirja = Annales entomologici Fennici 15: 101 - 120" title="Mitteilungen ueber die Apiden (Hym.) Finnlands. 3. Die Untergattung Taeniandrena Hedicke." volume="15" year="1949">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Niemelä">Niemelae</normalizedToken>
(1949)
</bibRefCitation>
, we keep 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae subsp. karelica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="subSpecies" species="gelriae" subSpecies="karelica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae karelica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="species" species="gelriae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, though the status of 
<taxonomicName family="Fabaceae" genus="A." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="A. gelriae subsp. karelica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" rank="subSpecies" species="gelriae" subSpecies="karelica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="375">A. gelriae karelica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires investigation given the cryptic diversity present in this group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="375">
This species is particularly challenging to identify in the female sex. Nearly all recent mentions from Switzerland (
<bibRefCitation author="Amiet, F" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="375" refId="B4" refString="Amiet, F, Herrmann, M, Mueller, A, Neumeyer, R, 2010. Apidae 6, Andrena, Melliturga, Panurginus, Panurgus. Fauna Helvetica 26, CSCF &amp; SEG (Neuchatel): 1-316." title="Apidae 6, Andrena, Melliturga, Panurginus, Panurgus. Fauna Helvetica 26, CSCF &amp; SEG (Neuchatel): 1 - 316." year="2010">Amiet et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
) were based on misidentified females.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
